main event: A series of more than ten but less than twenty bright, white lights arranged in a crescent shape were observed over San Antonio, Texas on March 30, 1952.
interesting points: The lights appeared to be very high intensity white lights that resembled fluorescent lights.
The relative position of the individual lights did not change, leading the observer to believe it was a single object.
The object had a bluish haze surrounding it and made no sound.
The object was estimated to be traveling at around 1,500 mph at an altitude between 10,000 and 20,000 feet.
The object was observed by multiple witnesses, including a Major from the 17th FER Air Force Base and a civilian named Mr. Sanjarne.
sighted object: Series of bright white lights in a crescent shape
witnesses: Multiple, including a military officer and civilian observers
photographs: No photographs included in the report
